<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

<h3>Are free AI image generators really free?</h3>
<p>Yes, they are genuinely free to use — no payment required. However, most impose limits on daily generations or feature access. Stable Diffusion is the only truly unlimited free option if you run it locally. Tools like Leonardo AI and Ideogram offer daily credit refreshes that let you keep generating indefinitely without paying, as long as you stay within the daily cap.</p>

<h3>Can I use free AI image generators commercially?</h3>
<p>Most free tiers permit some commercial use, but terms vary. Stable Diffusion's open-source license generally allows commercial use. DALL-E 3 grants full ownership of generated images. Leonardo AI allows commercial use on its free tier. Ideogram's free tier has some restrictions — check terms carefully. Always review each platform's specific license before using generated images in commercial projects.</p>

<h3>What about copyright for AI-generated images?</h3>
<p>AI-generated image copyright is a complex and evolving area of law. In the United States, the Copyright Office has stated that works created entirely by AI without human creative input may not qualify for copyright protection. Most AI generators grant you ownership of the output, but this doesn't necessarily equate to copyright protection. If you need legally protectable assets, consider incorporating meaningful human creative input and consult legal advice.</p>

<h3>Which free AI image generator is best for photorealistic images?</h3>
<p>DALL-E 3 (via ChatGPT's free tier) produces the most consistently photorealistic results among free options — excellent lighting, natural skin textures, and believable compositions. Stable Diffusion can match or exceed DALL-E 3's photorealism but requires technical setup, model selection, and often a good GPU. Leonardo AI's Realistic Vision model on the free tier also delivers impressive photorealistic results with minimal effort.</p>

<h3>Do free AI image generators add watermarks?</h3>
<p>Some do, some don't. DALL-E 3 via ChatGPT does not add visible watermarks. Stable Diffusion outputs have no watermarks since it's open-source. Leonardo AI's free tier may add watermarks to some generations — you can remove them by earning free credits through community participation. Ideogram adds watermarks on some free tier outputs. Check each tool's specific watermarking policy before committing to one.</p>

<h2>Final Verdict</h2>
<p>The era of high-quality free AI image generation is here. For most users, DALL-E 3 through ChatGPT's free tier offers the best balance of quality and ease of use — you get world-class image generation without spending a cent, albeit with daily limits.</p>
<p>If you need unlimited generations and don't mind some technical setup, Stable Diffusion is the ultimate free option. For game developers and asset creators, Leonardo AI's generous 150 daily credits and purpose-built tools make it the clear winner. And for anyone creating images with text — posters, ads, social media graphics — Ideogram's free tier is a clear standout.</p>
<p>Whichever tool you choose, there's never been a better time to explore AI image generation without opening your wallet.</p>
